name: Lost in the Shuffle by Nick Ouellette

metadata.name: Lost in the Shuffle #1
metadata.description:
Artist: Nick Ouellette

Edition: 1/1

Position in Collection: 1 of 28

Dimensions: 3111x4680

Collection Description: Nick created this collection of photographs ("Lost in the Shuffle") in the fall of 2010, as his semester-long project for the Introduction to Still Photography class he took at Harvard, taught by professor and photographer Chris Killip (1946-2020).  The collection is themed on the MBTA transit system in the greater Boston area and was originally printed as a 28 photo book and is being published as Nick's genesis NFT collection in the same order the photos appeared 11 years ago using the original .psd files
